1
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:10,080
You really worry me.

2
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,960
Dressed like this in a man's room,

3
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:17,880
it's improper.

4
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:19,539
Let's go. Come out with me.

5
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:23,440
Stop tugging at me. It's improper.

6
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:26,760
I did it to save you.

7
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:28,080
And I caught a cold.

8
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,240
In return,

9
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:35,240
you must brew the medicine for me yourself.

10
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,560
What? Is that a no?

11
00:01:41,039 --> 00:01:42,680
Fine, of course.

12
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,840
Let's go. Don't disturb Lord Fang's rest.

13
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,479
Yan'er, take care of Lord Fang.

14
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:47,280
Okay.

15
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,840
Why do you keep looking at me?

16
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:30,760
I think you look like Fang Ji's mother.

17
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:32,570
What do you mean?

18
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,440
Just now, you wiped his sweat,

19
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,040
and pressed his acupoints.

20
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:39,040
Isn't that just what happens when one is sick,

21
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,480
what a mother would do?

22
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,000
What?

23
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,920
Miss your mother?

24
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,640
You really are a rich young master.

25
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,760
You've only been away for a few days,

26
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:49,160
and you miss your mother.

27
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:56,760
Sorry.

28
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:00,760
Did I say the wrong thing again?

29
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:02,320
No.

30
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:07,720
I've actually never met my mother.

31
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,240
My father never tells me

32
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,640
what happened to her.

33
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,000
This...

34
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,860
was left to you by your mother.

35
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:27,560
Yes.

36
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,640
My father told me,

37
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,520
my mother embroidered this when I was born.

38
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,840
So whenever I miss her,

39
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:38,320
I trace the Qilin on it myself.

40
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,480
It's beautifully embroidered.

41
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,640
By the way,

42
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,080
I hunted a rabbit.

43
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,320
Your foot is injured.

44
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:03,280
I was afraid it would get cold.

45
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:06,080
I ordered them to make insoles from the rabbit fur.

46
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,820
I'll go see how they are doing.

47
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:08,600
Okay.

48
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:47,700
My Lord, you're awake.

49
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,250
Is my massage comfortable?

50
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,520
Shameless.

51
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:53,560
Have some self-respect.

52
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:56,480
Why do you speak to me like this?

53
00:04:57,159 --> 00:04:59,320
You never treated my sister like this.

54
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:00,760
Get out.

55
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:03,840
Get out.

56
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:27,940
Who is it? Do you not have eyes?

57
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:33,920
Forgive me, Little Marquis.

58
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,159
It's Miss Gu's sister.

59
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,120
This is the relay station.

60
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,640
Rushing around like this,

61
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:40,760
if you hurt someone,

62
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,420
you'd better watch your head.

63
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,520
Thank you for the reminder, Little Marquis.

64
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:45,560
Tell me,

65
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,640
Fang Erlang.

66
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,640
Who do you think you are?

67
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,440
A relative of the Emperor?

68
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,240
The world's number one scholar?

69
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:08,940
Or Imperial Preceptor Qin's beloved disciple?

70
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,040
You are nothing but a pawn.

71
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,240
Being played in the palm of others' hands,

72
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,720
without even knowing it.

73
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,760
Calm down, Lord Lu.

74
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,320
Xiong Renlian stole official salt.

75
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,920
The evidence is conclusive.

76
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:28,160
Moreover, you are related to the criminal.

77
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,760
You should have recused yourself from this case.

78
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,520
Haha.

79
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:35,840
Censor Fang, what great authority you have.

80
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,840
Xiong Renlian was a court official.

81
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,840
He died at home under suspicious circumstances.

82
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,320
As the Imperial Envoy,

83
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,980
how will you account for this?

84
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,850
If you want to keep investigating,

85
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:49,760
go ahead.

86
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,520
But let me remind you.

87
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,920
Think about

88
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:59,280
the fate of your benefactor, Lord Su Ziliang.

89
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:04,640
Do you think your mentor securing this position for you

90
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:06,760
was a favor?

91
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:08,810
If anything goes wrong,

92
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,520
he will only protect his own son.

93
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,520
As for you,

94
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:18,880
someone whose own father wishes he were dead,

95
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:22,240
who will have your back?

96
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,960
Watch your tongue, Lord Lu.

97
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:31,840
Why?

98
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,520
Did I touch a sore spot?

99
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,800
Lord Lu, you speak with such arrogance.

100
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,840
Obstructing an investigation,

101
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:45,320
threatening a court official...

102
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:46,159
Insolence!

103
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,080
Where did this wench come from?

104
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:49,940
How dare you speak such nonsense!

105
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:51,840
Xiong Renlian took bribes and bent the law.

106
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,080
He committed suicide to escape punishment.

107
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,520
As his uncle,

108
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,720
surely you cannot escape blame.

109
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,360
Who said it was suicide?

110
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,640
The coroner reported

111
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:07,560
that when Xiong died, his veins were bulging,

112
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,520
and his pupils were dilated.

113
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,680
He was clearly deranged.

114
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,760
There were even signs of sorcery.

115
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:19,520
So it was definitely murder.

116
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:25,080
Lord Fang, you are so eager to close the case.

117
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:29,040
Are you trying to claim credit before the Emperor?

118
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:34,039
So sorcery is that rampant in Jinzhou.

119
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,440
Just like that,

120
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:38,440
it can be used to murder a key criminal.

121
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:43,640
Lord Lu, you really govern this place well.

122
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,320
You...

123
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:46,880
Lord Lu,

124
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:50,520
why are you so knowledgeable about sorcery?

125
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:52,440
Lord Fang,

126
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:55,160
I suggest you write to the Emperor about this.

127
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,920
Let the expert on sorcery, Lord Lu,

128
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,840
assist in this case.

129
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,360
Stop this nonsense!

130
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,240
What sorcery?

131
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,720
I was just catching up with Lord Fang.

132
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,920
I won't interfere with official business.

133
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,120
Since it's just catching up,

134
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,040
then Lord Lu,

135
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:15,480
surely you won't mind if I find a storyteller

136
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,760
to spread the word

137
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:20,240
about the friendship you just showed Lord Fang?

138
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,160
You...

139
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:25,240
Since Lord Lu knows nothing about the sorcery case,

140
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,760
regarding today's events,

141
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,820
I, Fang, will let bygones be bygones.

142
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:29,940
But remember this.

143
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:33,880
I have my own bottom line and principles.

144
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:37,360
No one can shake them.

145
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:54,120
Thank you.

146
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,640
For what?

147
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,360
Here's to you.

148
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,680
Thank you for helping me out of that situation.

149
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,610
You're welcome.

150
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,160
I met the Young Marquis today.

151
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,760
He told me I look a lot like your mother.

152
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,280
Do I?

153
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:35,880
Yes.

154
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:41,880
Am I as gentle and kind as she was?

155
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,210
Beautiful and elegant?

156
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:44,680
Yes.

157
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:49,020
My mother has passed away.

158
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:53,160
I'm sorry.

159
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:56,640
It's fine.

160
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,920
My mother drowned when I was young.

161
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,320
Stop playing dumb. If you hadn't gone into the water,

162
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,760
Mother wouldn't have died.

163
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,880
There were no neighbors in the backyard.

164
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:09,600
You were afraid of punishment,

165
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,120
so you dared to blame an elder?

166
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,160
That's not true.

167
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,600
You were just playing around,

168
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,600
and tricked Mother into saving you.

169
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,800
You were pulled ashore,

170
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,640
but Mother drowned.

171
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,730
But, Father,

172
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,160
it really wasn't me.

173
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,040
Enough!

174
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,320
Your brother saw it with his own eyes.

175
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,560
Do you think he's lying?

176
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:29,840
Kneel properly.

177
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,300
Kneel before your mother.

178
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,560
My father was convinced

179
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:36,170
that I was the one who killed my mother.

180
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,200
Even now,

181
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,360
there is a rift between us.

182
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,080
Then all these years

183
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,400
must have been very hard for you.

184
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:53,020
Let's not talk about that.

185
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:56,960
The second bowl.

186
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,900
I want to apologize to you.

187
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:01,680
What for?

188
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:02,760
Drink this first.

189
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:13,000
There's something I've been keeping from you.

190
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,360
What is it?

191
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,560
We met when we were children.

192
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,000
When?

193
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:31,600
You and your father gave a little boy a bowl of porridge.

194
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:34,010
You even told him to drink more.

195
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,160
That was you?

196
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,040
You sure kept that a secret.

197
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,840
Back then, I had a falling out with my father.

198
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,760
So I came to the Capital alone.

199
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,960
I lost my money on the way,

200
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,160
lived on the streets,

201
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,690
and became a little beggar.

202
00:12:57,920 --> 00:13:00,520
It was you and your father who saved me.

203
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,880
Your father even sent me to the Capital.

204
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:07,820
That gave me the chance to study under Imperial Preceptor Qin.

205
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:19,560
Do you think fathers

206
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:22,560
are always good to outsiders

207
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:26,360
but bad to their own families?

208
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,570
That's not true.

209
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,000
Lord Su must

210
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,130
care deeply about you and Miss Yan'er.

211
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,480
He had his reasons.

212
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,720
I remember on the way to the Capital,

213
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:41,050
he kept talking about you and Miss Yan'er.

214
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:44,240
He told me he had two precious daughters,

215
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,040
and he'd do anything for them.

216
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,240
He said after the Witchcraft Case was settled,

217
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,320
he would take you two to travel the world.

218
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,780
I was so envious back then.

219
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,760
Now,

220
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,300
I really want to hug my father.

221
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,320
But I don't have the chance anymore.

222
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,520
But you still do.

223
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:14,720
Fang Ji.

224
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,800
Have you ever thought

225
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:22,480
that you and the Chancellor might be blinded by your own feelings?

226
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:27,080
If you don't truly hate him,

227
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,240
why torture each other?

228
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,200
Fang Ji.

229
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:52,600
Do you think a runaway slave girl

230
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:58,040
trying to clear the name of a criminal condemned by the Emperor,

231
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,120
is dreaming the impossible?

232
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:07,920
If I can clear my father's name,

233
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:12,160
will there be more

234
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,560
good officials like him?

235
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:19,280
And will the common people live better lives?

236
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:25,440
Don't worry.

237
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:31,240
I will be with you to exonerate the innocent.

238
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,720
To seek peace for the world.

239
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,440
My father named me Zhaoxue.

240
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,480
It must be the will of Heaven.

241
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,240
Blessed by destiny.

242
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,400
Success is certain.

243
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,320
Success.

244
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:49,400
Success.

245
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:59,640
A glance at misty rain, a dream.

246
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:06,520
Moonlight sings alone to the breeze.

247
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:10,490
The persistence of flowers blooming in the quiet night.

248
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:14,160
The promise made by the youth yesterday.

249
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,040
It is for love,

250
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,880
writing a page of deep emotion.
